# Harbor project rules

## Done means verify is green

Nothing is considered done until `npm run verify` passes (typecheck + lint + unit + integration). Do not open a PR or claim completion with a red verify gate.

## SPEC.md is the referee

Acceptance criteria live in [SPEC.md](../../SPEC.md). Implement to the spec; if behavior and SPEC disagree, update SPEC only when the product decision is intentional and documented in the same change.

## Never touch mainnet

Harbor may use mock, regtest, or **signet** only. Do not add mainnet RPC endpoints, mainnet explorers as defaults, or mainnet key material. Derivation may include mainnet vectors in unit tests only.

## Branch-per-slice, PR to main

- Work on a dedicated slice branch (e.g. `slice-3-signet`).
- Open a PR to `main` when verify is green.
- Do not commit directly to `main` unless the user explicitly asks.

## Fake money by default

Hosted / production demos stay on mock Bitcoin unless `HARBOR_NETWORK=signet` is explicitly set. Prefer fixture-based tests — no live network calls in CI.
